AllTray: Copyright 2004, Jochen Baier, email@jochen-baier.de


  With AllTray you can dock any application into the system tray/notification area.
  A high-light feature is that a click on the "close" button will minimize to system tray.
  It is written in C using GTK and Xlib. It works well with Gnome, KDE and XFCE4*.

  *XFCE CVS Version newer than Dec 15. 04



**Install:

  (./autogen.sh)
  ./configure
  make

  and as root:

  make install


**First Run:

  start AllTray with: 

  alltray --windowinfo


**Example programs:

  anjuta: Step 1, alltray anjuta -sw
  ding: Step 2, alltray --hints "Ding;ding;null" ding
  gcalctool: Step 1, alltray gcalctool
  gnome-terminal: Step 2 or Step 3,
      alltray --hints "Gnome-terminal;gnome-terminal;Terminal" gnome-terminal
  kcalc: Step 1, alltray kcalc
  kdict: Step 2, alltray --hints "Kdict;kdict;null" kdict
  kmail: Step 2,  alltray --hints "Kmail;kmail;null" kmail
  konqueror: Step 1, alltray konqueror
  konsole: Step 1, alltray konsole
  nautilus: Step 1, alltray nautilus
  thunderbird: Step 2, alltray --hints "Thunderbird-bin;Gecko;null" thunderbird
  valknut: Step 1, alltray -sw valknut --disable-tray
  xchat: Step 1, alltray xchat
  xmms: Step 3, alltray --hints "xmms;XMMS_Player;XMMS" xmms


**Help:

  alltray -h:
  
  usage: alltray [options] <program_name> [program parameter]
  
  where options include:
  
    --help; -h:  print this message\n"
    --show; -s:  do not hide window after start
    --hide_window; -hw: hide window during startup (experimental)
    --hints; -hi "WM_CLASS CLASS; WM_CLASS NAME; WM_NAME"
    --icon; -i  <path to png>: use this icon
    --windowinfo; -wi: get hints string by clicking on window
    --splashwindow; -sw: ignore splash window


**Requirements:
   
   Compile:
      
    - X Window stuff
    - GTK 2
   
   Run:
   
     - Gnome 2 with "Panel Notification Area" applet.
     - KDE (>= 3.3) with System tray.


